Top 1000 US Names Dataset

Top1000.Rd

A dataset containing the 1000 most common surnames in the United States, along with demographic breakdowns from the U.S. Census.

Usage

Top1000

Format

A tibble with 1000 rows and 11 variables:

name

Surname (character)

rank

Ranking by frequency (numeric)

count

Number of occurrences (numeric)

prop100k

Proportion per 100,000 people (numeric)

cum_prop100k

Cumulative proportion per 100,000 (numeric)

pct_white

Percent White (numeric)

pct_black

Percent Black (numeric)

pct_api

Percent Asian/Pacific Islander (numeric)

pct_aian

Percent American Indian/Alaska Native (numeric)

pct_two_or_more

Percent two or more races (numeric)

pct_hispanic

Percent Hispanic (numeric)

Source

U.S. Census Bureau, 2010 Census.
